The invention is explained by reference to the Examples in which mention is made of the following Figures:
Figure 1 is a schematic layout of a tubular reactor plant used to make the EVA polymer according to the invention referred to in the Examples;
Figure 2 is a temperature profile used to run the reactor of Figure 1 so as to provide the EVA copolymer according to the invention referred to in the Examples;
Figure 3A and 3B show a 13C NMR plots of the EVA copolymer according to the invention and a comparative grade UL00109 referred to in the Examples;
Figure 4 shows a graph plotting shear rate and viscosity for calculation of the relaxation time of the EVA copolymer according to the invention referred to in the Examples;
Figure 5 shows a bar chart indicating stretch hood relaxation and retained force at elevated temperatures (75% initial stretch - 60 % final stretch) of a film of the invention made using the EVA copolymer referred to in the Examples;
Figure 6A and 6B show graphs illustrating tear propagation behavior of different films including a film according to the invention; and
Figure 7 shows a three dimensional graph, illustrating of the effect on Coefficient of Friction of different amounts of Exceed polymer and film thickness of films according to the invention.
